<i> These glasses</i>
<i> could cost me an eye.</i>

13:22.702 --> 13:26.337
<i>If I wanted to be cool, I could</i>
<i>never wear my glasses again.</i>

13:28.275 --> 13:30.174
[indistinct chatter]

13:30.210 --> 13:34.112
[mark panting]

13:34.247 --> 13:37.315
-You okay?
-Yeah.

13:37.384 --> 13:39.183
I'm fine.

13:39.186 --> 13:40.251
[breathlessly]
yeah, fine.

13:41.354 --> 13:43.321
[inhales]

13:43.390 --> 13:46.024
-Where are your glasses?

13:46.026 --> 13:47.592
-I don't have glasses.

13:47.727 --> 13:51.729
-I thought you got glasses.
-Stop saying "glasses"!

13:51.731 --> 13:53.331
-What the frig?

13:54.734 --> 13:56.401
Children?

13:57.804 --> 14:03.140
I was inspired by the cross
mark has to bear.

14:03.176 --> 14:05.276
And I wanted to show you

14:05.345 --> 14:08.546
What it would be like
to be blind for the day.

14:08.548 --> 14:12.649
Now, even as I lose one sense,

14:12.651 --> 14:16.553
My other senses
become heightened.

14:16.590 --> 14:21.459
In the darkness,
can you see the light?

14:21.594 --> 14:23.428
Ritche: Uh, sister?

14:23.430 --> 14:25.729
-Whoever's talking,
I can hear you!

14:29.102 --> 14:30.268
-Sister...

14:30.403 --> 14:32.236
-Uh, I...

14:41.247 --> 14:45.082
-"then will the eyes
of the blind be opened."

14:45.118 --> 14:48.252
Isaiah 35:5.

14:48.255 --> 14:50.187
Sister perpetua!

14:50.257 --> 14:53.491
Where in god's name
are your students?

14:53.560 --> 14:55.059
-But I heard them!

14:55.095 --> 14:59.130
-One more mistake and I'll nail
you to<i> your</i> cross, sister!

14:59.265 --> 15:00.198
Now, go find them.

15:00.333 --> 15:01.799
-Yes, sister.

15:01.801 --> 15:03.668
Sorry, sister.

15:05.471 --> 15:07.205
Sister perpetua: Children?
Ready or not...

15:07.340 --> 15:09.040
-And mr. Critch?

15:09.175 --> 15:12.343
Where are your eye-glasses?

15:12.345 --> 15:14.646
-Uh, I...

15:14.781 --> 15:16.613
I don't have glasses, sister.

15:19.286 --> 15:20.685
Adult mark (v.O.):
<i> She didn't need glasses</i>

15:20.820 --> 15:23.220
<i>To see I was up to something.</i>

15:24.557 --> 15:28.092
And why is that, mr. Critch?

15:28.128 --> 15:30.361
Adult mark (v.O.):<i> Maybe I</i>
<i>should just tell her the truth.</i>

15:30.496 --> 15:32.296
<i> Maybe sister rose</i>
<i> would understand.</i>

15:32.332 --> 15:35.166
<i> Oh, who was I kidding?</i>

15:35.168 --> 15:38.770
-Dad-- dad said,
um, that...

15:38.772 --> 15:42.306
We couldn't afford them.

15:42.342 --> 15:45.309
Adult mark (v.O.):<i> What</i>
<i> the hell was I saying?</i>

15:45.345 --> 15:47.444
-Very well.

15:47.480 --> 15:51.249
If sister perpetua cannot ensure
you have what you need,

15:51.384 --> 15:53.785
I shall do so myself.

15:53.920 --> 15:56.687
[ominous music]

15:56.690 --> 15:58.589
Adult mark (v.O.):<i> I didn't</i>
<i> need glasses to see</i>

15:58.591 --> 16:00.725
<i> That something bad</i>
<i> was about to happen.</i>

16:06.666 --> 16:08.732
Adult mark (v.O.):<i> At home,</i>
<i> I loved my glasses.</i>

16:08.768 --> 16:10.535
-I always thought
we had a crappy tv,

16:10.670 --> 16:13.271
But the reception's
actually quite good!

16:13.406 --> 16:15.439
-Hey, buddy holly, right?

16:19.245 --> 16:21.279
Hey, dad.

16:21.414 --> 16:22.780
Guess what?

16:22.816 --> 16:24.682
I took a radio name.

16:24.817 --> 16:27.385
I'm mike campbell now.

16:27.520 --> 16:29.453
-Are you that
embarrassed of me?

16:29.489 --> 16:31.255
Adult mark (v.O.):
<i> At least with my glasses,</i>

16:31.257 --> 16:33.157
<i> I'd have a clear view</i>
<i> of the show.</i>

16:33.293 --> 16:34.492
-Your father's a bit upset.

16:34.561 --> 16:36.394
-Turned his back
on his family.

16:36.463 --> 16:37.828
He's insulted his father.

16:37.864 --> 16:39.897
-When's supper?
-Oh, will you shut it?

16:39.899 --> 16:42.433
Mark: Pop, mike changed
his name, to "campbell."

16:42.469 --> 16:45.803
-Oh.
Was mike "boy-ar-dee" taken?

16:45.938 --> 16:48.873
Mike sr: What kind of person
gives up their surname, hm?

16:48.875 --> 16:50.875
-Well, I gave up mine
to marry you.

16:50.877 --> 16:52.376
-That's different!

16:52.379 --> 16:54.245
-Everybody thinks
I've got a free pass

16:54.314 --> 16:56.280
Just 'cause of
who my old man is!

16:56.316 --> 16:59.250
-Well, I'm sorry for giving you
an opportunity I never had!

16:59.252 --> 17:00.551
-What's that
supposed to mean?

17:00.687 --> 17:02.853
-Dad, I gotta be me.

17:02.922 --> 17:05.756
-And who the hell is that?
-I don't know, okay?

17:05.759 --> 17:09.827
But I'm not gonna find out
if I keep living in your shadow!

17:09.863 --> 17:12.830
I just need to know
if I'm any good on my own.

17:12.965 --> 17:15.866
-Oh, don't be so foolish.
You're the best I've ever seen!

17:15.935 --> 17:20.004
♪

17:20.006 --> 17:22.473
♪

17:22.608 --> 17:24.374
Pop: Oh, jesus.

17:26.379 --> 17:27.845
I think I'll change<i> my</i> name.

17:27.980 --> 17:30.348
-Oh, mike.

17:30.483 --> 17:31.682
And mike.

17:31.684 --> 17:33.417
My mikes!

17:33.420 --> 17:34.352
[knock at door]

17:34.487 --> 17:35.853
Who the frig's at the door?

17:35.855 --> 17:37.622
Mark!
Get that, hm?

17:37.757 --> 17:39.190
-Yeah.

17:39.325 --> 17:40.958
[ominous music]

17:40.960 --> 17:42.627
Oh!

17:42.629 --> 17:43.961
Hello, mr. Critch.

17:43.963 --> 17:45.696
Adult mark (v.O.):
<i> A nun at the house?</i>

17:45.832 --> 17:47.564
<i>I'd never seen one in the wild!</i>

17:47.600 --> 17:49.567
-I was just going to
drop off a hamper

17:49.569 --> 17:51.935
For your family
in their time of need,

17:51.971 --> 17:55.973
But I see that your
fortunes have changed.

17:55.975 --> 17:59.710
I think we can both see things
more clearly now.

17:59.712 --> 18:01.712
-I can explain.
I--I only just--

18:01.714 --> 18:03.681
-Oh, sister rose!
What a surprise!

18:03.816 --> 18:05.316
Are you coming in?

18:05.451 --> 18:06.884
Adult mark (v.O.):
<i> Don't invite her in!</i>

18:06.886 --> 18:08.652
<i> Everyone knows that dracula</i>
<i> has to be invited!</i>

18:08.721 --> 18:09.987
-Oh, no.

18:09.989 --> 18:12.990
I just wanted to check
on mark's glasses.

18:13.059 --> 18:14.458
-Oh!
-No troubles?

18:14.494 --> 18:18.529
-No, he loves them.

18:18.664 --> 18:20.264
Is that for us?

18:20.333 --> 18:21.332
-No.

18:21.467 --> 18:24.235
Pop: Well, well, well!

18:24.304 --> 18:27.338
What's in the basket,
little blue riding hood?

18:27.473 --> 18:28.873
Ooh!

18:28.942 --> 18:31.808
What luscious
big lips you've got!

18:31.845 --> 18:33.511
Awoooooo!

18:33.513 --> 18:34.679
-Uh...

18:34.814 --> 18:37.882
You'll see me, uh,
tomorrow, mr. Critch.

18:37.951 --> 18:40.417
And I will be...
Watching... You.

18:40.419 --> 18:42.419
[pop laughs]

18:42.489 --> 18:44.488
-What in the flying
friggity-frig

18:44.524 --> 18:46.557
Was that all about?

18:46.593 --> 18:47.558
Jeez!

18:49.028 --> 18:50.695
Adult mark (v.O.):
<i> Like it or not,</i>

18:50.697 --> 18:52.897
<i> You have to learn</i>
<i> to embrace the new you.</i>

18:54.601 --> 18:56.500
<i> You'll never see everything.</i>

18:56.536 --> 18:58.435
-If you so much as
looks at him funny again,

18:58.437 --> 18:59.970
I'll kick you
in the arse so hard,

19:00.039 --> 19:02.640
My shoelaces will be
coming out your nose.

19:02.642 --> 19:04.508
[bus door opens]

19:04.511 --> 19:09.447
♪

19:09.582 --> 19:13.451
♪

19:13.586 --> 19:17.521
♪

19:22.395 --> 19:24.562
Fox: You're wearing them!

19:24.631 --> 19:26.797
I wanna try 'em on.

19:26.866 --> 19:29.433
-Oh... Uh...
They're a medical aid!

19:29.502 --> 19:31.835
-Whoa, I can see your bones!

19:31.871 --> 19:33.671
-Yeah, I know I'm a nerd.

19:33.740 --> 19:35.873
-I was just foolin'.

19:35.875 --> 19:37.975
Come on, put 'em on for me.

19:38.110 --> 19:40.411
Please?

19:40.480 --> 19:44.982
♪

19:45.018 --> 19:47.752
I think they look...

19:47.754 --> 19:49.754
Handsome.

19:51.758 --> 19:56.026
So... I guess I need
glasses now, too, huh?

19:56.095 --> 19:57.428
-Wait...

19:59.032 --> 20:00.364
You're a girl?

20:00.433 --> 20:02.666
-Shut it!

20:02.702 --> 20:03.901
-I mean...

20:05.305 --> 20:06.437
Adult mark (v.O.):<i> If only</i>
<i>they made glasses that let us</i>

20:06.439 --> 20:08.071
<i> See ourselves</i>
<i> the way others do.</i>

20:14.046 --> 20:16.781
Adult mark (v.O.):<i> When</i>
<i> we accept who we are,</i>

20:16.916 --> 20:20.451
<i> The way forward has a way</i>
<i> of coming into focus...</i>

20:22.088 --> 20:24.755
<i> So we can see</i>
<i> the writing on the wall.</i>

20:24.791 --> 20:27.058
♪

20:27.060 --> 20:30.361
♪

20:30.496 --> 20:35.399
♪

20:35.468 --> 20:38.602
♪

20:38.638 --> 20:40.137
Adult mark (v.O.):
<i> So we can see things</i>

20:40.206 --> 20:43.541
<i> From another perspective.</i>

20:45.144 --> 20:48.079
<i> And we can see people</i>
<i> for who they really are.</i>

20:48.081 --> 20:49.480
-And that's the news!

20:49.549 --> 20:51.882
Stay tuned for the top ten
at ten, with mike...

20:52.018 --> 20:54.852
Campbell.

20:54.921 --> 20:58.889
-And mike critch will be back
with more news on the hour.

20:58.925 --> 21:01.492
The beach boys have fallen
from the top spot this week

21:01.561 --> 21:04.094
Into third, with "kokomo"...

21:04.130 --> 21:07.898
♪

21:07.967 --> 21:09.567
Adult mark (v.O.):<i> And besides,</i>

21:09.702 --> 21:11.636
<i> All the truly beautiful</i>
<i> things in life</i>

21:11.771 --> 21:14.171
<i> Are invisible anyway.</i>

21:14.173 --> 21:17.174
♪

